It does sound like an excellent possibility to be able to map out the universe in radiance from a single particle or even a few; but when I dive into these questions I start to wonder how this car sized AI would begin to behave once it has reach unknown territory in the quantum world wherein there is no immediate solution that allows it to render  !new cross word puzzles’ for it to complete. Using cross word puzzles as an analogy serves a more significant role in this case because I would imagine the sheer volume of what we are imagining here is more than one car sized intelligence could theoretically compute within the time space continum. My guess is that the intelligence would run into time scales that aren't rehearsable with the observable universe, and so a multidimensional theatre would be opened in where different neuropathways would in turn be displayed as a result. Things that didn't actually happen if the intelligence becomes divergent in the process, so in that case; 

The intelligence would essentially be creating within itself an entirely new basin of information that extends beyond its observational array within the continuum.

Perhaps in that experience and experimental approach; there would increase the number of car sized intelligences in order to fully understand the radicals within the quantum field of study. That's my take any how.
